FBIS4-62052 "drsov092_d_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 Regional Affairs Southern Metals Giant Shuts Down for Want of Capital Southern Metals Giant Shuts Down for Want of Capital PM1105113594 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 11 May 94 p 1 PM1105113594 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [ITAR-TASS report: "Taganrog Metallurgical Plant Halted"] [Text] The Taganrog Metallurgical Plant, the largest enterprise in southern Russia, closed on Tuesday. It specialized in the production of pipes, mainly for the oil industry. The main reason for the closure is that consumers owe the plant more than 20 billion rubles for output. The Taganrog plant does not have the means to pay for fuel for the open-hearth furnaces.
